dreisoft.tresos.datamodel2.api.model

Class ImporterInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • dreisoft.tresos.datamodel2.api.model.ImporterInfo

  • public class ImporterInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    Instances of this class represent one entry of the attribute IMPORTER_INFO attached to a DCtxt. If there are multiple ImporterInfos at the same DCtxt, they may not contradict each other - e.g. Any.CALCULATED may be combined with Any.DEFAULT_VALUE

    Beside the type of the importer (which can be queried via getType()), there can be any number of additional data provided by the service, wizard, importer or component providing the importer info 
     Valid Examples for IMPORTER_INFO node attribute value:
 
  @CALC
  @CALC(SvcAs)
  @CALC(SvcAs,myService)
  @CALC(SvcAs,myService,1.0.5)
 
 NOTE: only calculated parameters may have additional data (shown in brackets)
    To set an ImporterInfo to a DCtxt, use method DCtxt.any and there Any.setImporterInfo(int, String...)
    Since:
    20.0
